SUMMARY:Investigate missing narratives in new batch pipeline run
DESCRIPTION:Trend narratives ran on 2026-03-24 (9 narratives) but not on 2026-03-25 post-collect run.\n\nInvestigate:\n- run_trending.py --narratives flag: is it passed in run_pipeline.py stages?\n- Is the narratives stage skipped when collect exits rc=2 (batch_pending path)?\n- Does make post-collect pass --narratives to run_trending.py?\n- Check funnel_stats for 2026-03-25 trending stage drop_reasons\n- OPENAI_API_KEY not set warning seen in screenshot — narratives currently require OpenAI; should switch to Anthropic\n\nCommands:\n  sqlite3 data/db/film.db "SELECT * FROM funnel_stats WHERE stage='trending' ORDER BY run_date DESC LIMIT 5;"\n  grep -n "narratives" scripts/run_pipeline.py\n  grep -n "narratives" scripts/run_trending.py
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:task-uzel-auth-20260325@predictor_ingest
DTSTAMP:20260325T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260325
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260326
SUMMARY:Design standalone secure login for UZEL hub preview access
DESCRIPTION:Design a lightweight, standalone authentication layer to control who can preview the UZEL hub graph explorer.\n\nDiscussion points:\n- Approach options:\n  A) Static passphrase in URL (?token=xxx) — simplest, no server needed\n  B) Nginx basic auth — one config line, credentials in .htpasswd\n  C) Cloudflare Access — zero-trust, free tier, Google/GitHub SSO\n  D) Simple token list in a JSON file checked by a thin Express/FastAPI gate\n\n- Requirements to clarify:\n  * How many preview users? (handful vs dozens)\n  * Should access be per-domain or global?\n  * Is SSO (Google/GitHub login) acceptable or does it need to be credential-only?\n  * Does the server have a domain name / TLS cert already?\n  * Hetzner VPS — is Nginx already serving the web/ directory?\n\n- Constraint: must not require changes to the static Cytoscape.js client\n- Preferred: no new long-running processes if avoidable
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
